>Do you want to know how to rank higher on search engines and drive more traffic to your website? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Weve handpicked 30+ amazing SEO hacks to help you get more organic traffic and improve your search rankings on Google in no time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Since this is a long post with many high-value SEO tips, weve organized them into categories for you. You can click the category to skip ahead to the section youre interested in:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#on-page-seo-hacks\">On-Page SEO Hacks: Maximize Organic Traffic</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-use-the-right-seo-tools\">1. Use the Right SEO Plugin</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-1-increase-ctr-by-adding-the-year-to-your-seo-title\">2. Increase CTR By Adding the Year to Your SEO Title</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-2-optimize-your-images-with-descriptive-alt-text\">3. Optimize Your Images with Descriptive Alt Text</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-3-make-your-urls-seo-friendly\">4. Make Your URLs SEO-Friendly</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-4-unlock-more-traffic-by-adding-related-keywords-to-your-content\">5. Unlock More Traffic by Adding Related Keywords to Your Content</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-5-write-descriptive-meta-descriptions-to-boost-rankings\">6. Write Descriptive Meta Descriptions to Boost Rankings</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-add-meta-descriptions-in-wordpress-using-ai\">How to Add Meta Descriptions in WordPress Using AI</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-manually-add-meta-descriptions-in-wordpress\">How to Manually Add Meta Descriptions in WordPress</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-6-create-an-xml-sitemap-to-help-google-find-your-new-content\">7. Create an XML Sitemap to Help Google Find Your New Content</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-7-use-schema-markup-and-rank-for-google-rich-snippets\">8. Use Schema Markup to Rank for Google Rich Snippets</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-check-for-broken-links\">9. Check for and Fix Broken Links</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-8-use-an-seo-checklist-to-optimize-your-website\">10. Use an SEO Checklist to Optimize Your Website</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-9-spy-on-your-competitors-and-steal-their-keyword-ideas\">11. Spy on Your Competitors and Steal Their Keyword Ideas</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#site-speed-seo-hacks\">Site Speed SEO Hacks: Optimize for Speed and User Experience (UX)</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-10-install-a-cache-plugin-to-increase-page-loading\">12. Install a Cache Plugin to Increase Page Loading</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-11-compress-your-images-to-reduce-file-size\">13. Compress Your Images to Reduce File Size</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-12-use-a-cdn-to-improve-site-speed-even-more\">14. Use a CDN to Improve Site Speed Even More</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-13-make-your-site-mobile-friendly-using-a-responsive-theme\">15. Make Your Site Mobile-Friendly Using a Responsive Theme</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#content-seo-hacks\">Content SEO Hacks: Get Traffic From Existing Content</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-14-use-long-tail-keywords-to-get-more-organic-traffic\">16. Use Long-Tail Keywords to Get More Organic Traffic</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-optimizing-your-content-for-long-tail-keywords\">Optimizing Your Content for Long-Tail Keywords</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-15-improve-readability-and-keep-visitors-on-your-site\">17. Improve Readability and Keep Visitors on Your Site</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-improve-readability-using-aioseo\">Improve Readability Using AIOSEO</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-16-help-google-discover-your-new-content-with-internal-linking\">18. Help Google Discover Your New Content With Internal Linking</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-internal-linking-made-easy-with-aioseo\">Internal Linking Made Easy with AIOSEO</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-17-repurpose-your-existing-content-into-a-podcast\">19. Repurpose Your Existing Content Into a Podcast</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-18-get-conversational-and-optimize-for-voice-search\">20. Get Conversational and Optimize for Voice Search</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-19-increase-conversions-by-linking-your-rss-feed\">21. Increase Conversions by Linking Your RSS Feed</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-20-optimize-your-video-content-and-rank-in-video-search\">22. Optimize Your Video Content and Rank in Video Search</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-monitor-content-performance\">23. Monitor Content and Keyword Performance</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#social-networks-seo-hacks\">Social Networks SEO Hacks: Get More Referral Traffic</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-21-let-google-know-about-your-social-media-profiles\">24. Let Google Know About Your Social Media Profiles</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-22-add-twitter-cards-and-facebook-thumbnails\">25. Add Twitter Cards and Facebook Thumbnails</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-23-add-social-feeds-to-your-site-and-improve-organic-reach\">26. Add Social Feeds to Your Site and Improve Organic Reach</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-24-encourage-user-generated-content-and-get-free-marketing\">27. Encourage User-Generated Content and Get Free Marketing</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-25-reply-to-comments-and-get-more-returning-visitors\">28. Reply to Comments and Get More Returning Visitors</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#local-seo-hacks\">Local SEO Hacks: Boost Rankings on Google Maps</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-26-get-featured-on-googles-knowledge-panel-and-google-maps\">29. Get Featured on Googles Knowledge Panel and Google Maps</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-27-build-and-optimize-your-citations\">30. Build and Optimize Your Citations</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-28-submit-your-site-to-high-quality-local-directories\">31. Submit Your Site to High-Quality Local Directories</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#off-page-seo-hacks\">Off-Page SEO Hacks: Winning Backlink Strategies</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-29-look-for-guest-blogging-opportunities-to-get-backlinks\">32. Look for Guest Blogging Opportunities to Get Backlinks</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-30-create-and-add-infographics-to-your-site\">33. Create and Add Infographics to Your Site</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-use-these-30-seo-hacks-and-tips-to-boost-your-rankings-and-revenue\">Use these 30+ SEO Hacks and Tips to Boost Your Rankings and Revenue</a></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s start by walking you through some actionable on-page SEO hacks to help you maximize your organic traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"3 SEO Tricks To Help Grow Your Traffic\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/LDiKh_pEGlA?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"on-page-seo-hacks\">On-Page SEO Hacks: Maximize Organic Traffic</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>On-page SEO includes everything you&#8217;re doing on your own website to optimize it to rank higher in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the right on-page SEO hacks, you can help Google understand your content better and match it with the people who are searching for it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few quick hacks to boost your on-page SEO and get more traffic!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-use-the-right-seo-tools\">1. Use the Right SEO Plugin</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the first steps to winning at SEO is to use the right SEO plugin. For WordPress users, it doesnt get better than <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"311\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-2.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO homepage\" class=\"wp-image-185607\" title=\"AIOSEO is a powerful tool that can help you maintain the links on your site.\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-2.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-2-300x133.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-2-600x267.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-2-135x60.png 135w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-2-203x90.png 203w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">AIOSEO</a> is a powerful yet easy-to-use SEO plugin that has been downloaded over 100 million times. Millions of smart bloggers use AIOSEO to help them boost their search engine rankings and drive qualified traffic to their blogs. Thats because the plugin has many powerful features and modules designed to help you properly configure your SEO settings. Examples include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Search Statistics:</strong> This powerful Google Search Console integration lets you track your keyword rankings and see important SEO metrics with 1-click, and more.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Next-gen Schema generator</strong>: This no-code schema generator enables users to generate and output any schema markup on your site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Redirection Manager</strong>: Helps you manage redirects and eliminate 404 errors, making it easier for search engines to crawl and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/index-your-website-on-google/\">index your site</a>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Link Assistant</strong>: Powerful internal linking tool that <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-link-assistant-can-save-you-time-on-internal-and-external-link-building/\">automates building links</a> between pages on your site. It also gives you an audit of outbound links.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SEO Preview</strong>: This gives you an overview of your search and social snippets and general SEO so you can improve your optimization.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>IndexNow:</strong> For fast indexing on search engines that support the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-is-indexnow-for-seo/\">IndexNow protocol</a> (like Bing and Yandex).</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Sitemap generator</strong>: Automatically generate <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">different types of sitemaps</a> to notify all search engines of any updates on your site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/\">And more</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO also has other powerful tools to help you master your on-page SEO, off-page SEO, and even technical SEO. The best part about AIOSEO is that its a no-code SEO plugin. This means you can use it to perform most SEO tasks even if you dont have any technical or coding knowledge.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on how to install AIOSEO, check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">installation guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out our article on the <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-plugins-for-wordpress/\">best WordPress SEO plugins</a> for more tools.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-1-increase-ctr-by-adding-the-year-to-your-seo-title\">2. Increase CTR By Adding the Year to Your SEO Title</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that the more people click on your site in search results, the higher you&#8217;re likely to rank?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding the year to your SEO title is an excellent way to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-to-increase-your-organic-clickthrough-rates/\" title=\"8 Proven Ways to Increase Your Organic Clickthrough Rates\">increase your click-through rate</a> (CTR). It helps users see that your content is fresh and current, which Google and other search engines favor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This strategy will work best for content already ranking on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-are-serps/\" title=\"What Are SERPs (And Why Are they Important to SEO)?\">search engine results pages</a> (SERPs) since boosting your CTR can help move you up in rankings on the 1st page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding the current year to your SEO title is easy when using AIOSEO. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, scroll down in the post or page youre editing to the <strong>AIOSEO Settings</strong> and go to the <strong>Post Title</strong> section.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"359\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-variables-to-your-seo-title-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Adding variables to your SEO title in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31680\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-variables-to-your-seo-title-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-variables-to-your-seo-title-in-aioseo-300x148.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-variables-to-your-seo-title-in-aioseo-600x295.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can click on the different tags to insert variables into your SEO title. For example, if you click on the + Post Title tag, AIOSEO automatically adds your posts title as an SEO title.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Snippet Preview</strong> above the Post Title shows an example of how your SEO title will look in the SERPs (Search Engine Result Pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, click on the + Post Title tag, and itll open a drop-down menu where you can choose to add the <strong>Current Year </strong>to your SEO title.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-current-year-to-your-seo-title-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Adding the current year to your SEO title in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31681\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-current-year-to-your-seo-title-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-current-year-to-your-seo-title-in-aioseo-300x148.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-current-year-to-your-seo-title-in-aioseo-600x296.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply click on it, and the Current Year is added!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now the year will be updated automatically for you &#8211; no need to spend time updating it yourself.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you prefer, you can also type in your SEO title and year directly in the Post Title field.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-2-optimize-your-images-with-descriptive-alt-text\">3. Optimize Your Images with Descriptive Alt Text</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Alt text or alternative text is crucial for SEO. It helps Google understand what your images are about. As well as helps visitors to get information about your images if they cant be displayed on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Alt text is an HTML attribute thats added to the image tag, which is used to show images on a page.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It can look like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;img src=\"img_playful-black-kitten.jpg\" <strong>alt=\"Playful black kitten\"</strong> width=\"500\" height=\"600\"&gt;</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>When writing your alt text, you should describe your image as clearly as possible. Dont just use one or two words to write your alt text. Instead, imagine how you would describe your images to a blind person.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, rather than using just cake&#8217; use milk chocolate ice cream cake. This will also help Google to rank your image in image searches.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But dont stuff your alt text with similar keywords thinking itll help you rank higher. In fact, it can result in the opposite, and Google may see your site as spam.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can easily add your alt text in the WordPress block editor. Simply scroll down in the post or page youre editing, and click on your image so that it gets marked with the blue frame. Then, go to the <strong>Image Settings </strong>in the right column of your editor, and type in your alt text in the <strong>Alt Text (alternative text) field.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"367\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-alt-text-in-wordpress-block-editor.png\" alt=\"Adding alt text in WordPress block editor\" class=\"wp-image-31218\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-alt-text-in-wordpress-block-editor.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-alt-text-in-wordpress-block-editor-300x151.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-alt-text-in-wordpress-block-editor-600x302.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is an easy step in boosting your <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-best-optimize-images-in-wordpress\">image SEO</a>, but that&#8217;s often overlooked. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-3-make-your-urls-seo-friendly\">4. Make Your URLs SEO-Friendly</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An SEO-friendly URL describes the page using keywords that are easy to read for both search engines and users. It should provide a good user experience and tell search engines what the page is about.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Heres an example of an SEO-friendly URL:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>http:&#47;&#47;www.example.com/how-to-make-a-website</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>This URL is short, organized, and easy to read. Search engines and users can tell what the page is about.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the other hand, unoptimized URLs are random and hard to read or remember. They usually include numbers, letters, and special characters.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like this one:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>https:&#47;&#47;www.example.com/?p=10467</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>To ensure your WordPress site&#8217;s URLs are SEO-friendly, head over to <strong>Settings  Permalinks</strong> and mark the <strong>Post name</strong> option.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wordpress-seo-friendly-permalinks.png\" alt=\"Permalink settings in WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-31691\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wordpress-seo-friendly-permalinks.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wordpress-seo-friendly-permalinks-300x169.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wordpress-seo-friendly-permalinks-600x338.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While this URL structure is SEO-friendly, it doesnt apply to all websites.&nbsp;For example, a news publication site might need a URL with the day and name. Or a large site with hundreds of articles might need a custom structure.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can check out WPBeginner&#8217;s post on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/seo-friendly-url-structure-for-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SEO-friendly URL structure for WordPress</a> to find the best URL structure for your business.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, dont put dates or years in your URLs. This makes it more difficult to re-feature old content, and users may think your content is old even after updating it. Youll also save yourself the extra effort of redirecting your URLs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-4-unlock-more-traffic-by-adding-related-keywords-to-your-content\">5. Unlock More Traffic by Adding Related Keywords to Your Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Its crucial to use the right keyword variations to increase your organic traffic and climb in rankings on Google. More importantly, you need to try and understand the intent behind what your users are searching for and optimize your content accordingly.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step is creating easy-to-read, high-quality content that uses related keywords. This also helps Google to understand the meaning or intent behind your content and match it with more searches.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, the more keyword variations you use in your content, the more searches you can rank for and the more traffic youll unlock!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can easily find more keywords using AIOSEOs <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/introducing-semrush-integration/\" title=\"Introducing Semrush Integration: Add Additional Keyphrases to Boost SEO\">Semrush integration. It will suggest</a> additional keywords and give you the search volume and trends straight from the screen.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply scroll down in the post or page youre editing below your <strong>Focus Keyphrase</strong> and click the <strong>Get Additional Keyphrases</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"419\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/get-additional-keyphrases-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Get additional keyphrases in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31682\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/get-additional-keyphrases-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/get-additional-keyphrases-in-all-in-one-seo-300x172.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/get-additional-keyphrases-in-all-in-one-seo-600x344.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open a new window where you can view suggestions for <strong>Additional Keyphrases.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"359\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/additional-keyphrases-by-semrush.png\" alt=\"Additional keyphrases by Semrush in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-30305\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/additional-keyphrases-by-semrush.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/additional-keyphrases-by-semrush-300x148.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/additional-keyphrases-by-semrush-600x295.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new keyphrase will be added to your content with a single click of the <strong>Add Keyphrase</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, its never been easier to rank for more keywords and dominate the search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-5-write-descriptive-meta-descriptions-to-boost-rankings\">6. Write Descriptive Meta Descriptions to Boost Rankings</h3>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"block-728b70e0-7e8d-48c8-9a27-f533314a456d\">The meta description is an HTML tag that summarizes a pages content. Its purpose is to provide a short description of your page for search engines and users searching for content in the SERPs. Because of this, they are an essential part of SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Heres an example of AIOSEOs meta description from the search results on Google:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"174\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/meta-description-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Example of meta description for All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31685\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/meta-description-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/meta-description-all-in-one-seo-300x72.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/meta-description-all-in-one-seo-600x143.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Today, Google mainly focuses on the user experience, so a good meta description should explain what your post or page is about. It should also appeal to users and encourage them to click on your search listing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, a good meta description should:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Describe your pages content</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Answers users questions&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Include a call to action</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Be unique and interesting</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Include your main or focus keyword</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, it cant include all of the above at the same time. But depending on your page&#8217;s topic, you need to write as descriptive and interesting meta descriptions as possible to increase your CTR and boost rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-how-to-add-meta-descriptions-in-wordpress-using-ai\">How to Add Meta Descriptions in WordPress Using AI</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, you can automatically add meta descriptions to your articles using the&nbsp; <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/our-openai-integration-just-got-10x-more-affordable-now-using-chatgpt/\">AI Title/Description Generator</a>. This is a powerful tool powered by ChatGPT. The AI Title/Description Generator takes the labor out of crafting <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-title-tags/\">post titles</a> and meta descriptions, all with just the click of a button!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All you have to do to use this game-changing <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-meta-description-generator-in-wordpress/\">meta description generator</a> is click on the robot icon next to the <strong>Meta Description</strong> field.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"267\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-5.png\" alt=\"Click the robot icon to generate 5 meta description suggestions using AI.\" class=\"wp-image-185616\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-5.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-5-300x114.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-5-600x228.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-5-158x60.png 158w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-5-237x90.png 237w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"462\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-6.png\" alt=\"Select your favorite AI-generated meta description\" class=\"wp-image-185617\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-6.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-6-300x197.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-6-600x395.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-6-91x60.png 91w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image-6-137x90.png 137w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Select the one you want by clicking the + button and tweak it according to your taste.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on using this powerful meta description generator, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-a-meta-description-generator-in-wordpress/\">check out this guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-how-to-manually-add-meta-descriptions-in-wordpress\">How to Manually Add Meta Descriptions in WordPress</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also manually craft your meta description directly in the <strong>Meta Description</strong> field.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"179\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/entering-meta-description-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Entering your meta description in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31687\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/entering-meta-description-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/entering-meta-description-in-aioseo-300x74.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/entering-meta-description-in-aioseo-600x147.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Dont forget to include the primary or focus keyword that you want to rank for.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also use any of the pre-installed tags to insert different variables. For example, the <strong>+ Post Excerpt </strong>automatically adds your posts excerpt to your meta description.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"181\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-your-meta-description-in-aioseo.png\" alt=\"Adding your meta description in All in One SEO using variables\" class=\"wp-image-31688\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-your-meta-description-in-aioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-your-meta-description-in-aioseo-300x74.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/adding-your-meta-description-in-aioseo-600x149.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And AIOSEO even gives you the max recommended characters for your meta description. If you use more characters, your meta description will be cut off in the search result pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-write-meta-descriptions-for-seo/\" title=\"How to Write Meta Descriptions for SEO (Boost CTR &amp; Rankings)\">Check out this tutorial</a> for detailed instructions on crafting meta descriptions that boost SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-6-create-an-xml-sitemap-to-help-google-find-your-new-content\">7. Create an XML Sitemap to Help Google Find Your New Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An XML sitemap lists every new and important URL on your website. In other words, it helps Google to find and crawl your new content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With AlOSEO, you can easily create an XML sitemap and send it to all popular search engines. In fact, once youve <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">installed and activated</a> AIOSEO, it automatically generates a sitemap for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All you need to do is check if its enabled by navigating to <strong>All in One SEO menu  Sitemaps </strong>and clicking the <strong>General Sitemap</strong> tab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"General sitemap menu in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31227\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-600x353.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open the General Sitemap window, where you can see that the <strong>Enable Sitemap</strong> option is set to on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"346\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Enable XML sitemap in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31228\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x284.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Thats it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, if you use videos on your website, you can create a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-video-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/\">video sitemap</a> to make sure Google finds your video content. And if you have a news website, you can create a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/\">news sitemap</a> that automatically gets submitted to Google News.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-7-use-schema-markup-and-rank-for-google-rich-snippets\">8. Use Schema Markup to Rank for Google Rich Snippets</h3>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"block-7f11f71a-2f50-4d72-9b8e-c431fd9368fc\">Youve probably seen those nice-looking rich search results on Google with star ratings and prices or questions and answers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"block-7f11f71a-2f50-4d72-9b8e-c431fd9368fc\">Google rich snippets can help you unlock the highest rankings and traffic for your site without you having to be an SEO expert. They allow you to add additional information about your pages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part is that adding schema markup is super easy with AIOSEO&#8217;s <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-aioseo-4-2-5-next-gen-schema-generator-to-improve-your-seo-rankings/\" title=\"Announcing AIOSEO 4.2.5: Next-Gen Schema Generator to Improve Your SEO Rankings\">Next-gen Schema Generator</a>. This no-code module adds the schema code for you in the background. All you have to do is choose your schema type in the <strong>Schema Catalog</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"472\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/schema-generator-catalog.png\" alt=\"AIOSEO\'s Schema Catalog has most of the popular schema types.\" class=\"wp-image-132311\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/schema-generator-catalog.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/schema-generator-catalog-300x202.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/schema-generator-catalog-600x405.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-schema-markup-to-wordpress-without-a-plugin/\" title=\"How to Add Schema Markup to WordPress Without a Plugin\">Check out this tutorial</a> for detailed instructions on adding schema markup in WordPress. </p>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"block-7f11f71a-2f50-4d72-9b8e-c431fd9368fc\">Heres an example of some of the rich snippets you can generate. The first one below is generated from <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-schema-recipe-markup-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add Schema Recipe Markup in WordPress [The Easy Way]\">recipe schema</a>:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"358\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/recipe-rich-snippet.png\" alt=\"Example of recipe rich snippet on Google\" class=\"wp-image-26196\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/recipe-rich-snippet.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/recipe-rich-snippet-300x147.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/recipe-rich-snippet-600x294.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Looks good, right?!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, they show additional information like star ratings, cooking time, and ingredients straight from the search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, your listings get more noticeable on SERPs, so youre likely to drive more organic traffic to your site and increase sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Heres another example of a <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-an-faq-section-in-wordpress-2-super-easy-ways/\" title=\"How to Add an FAQ Section in WordPress (2 Super Easy Ways)\">rich snippet for FAQs</a>:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"337\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs.png\" alt=\"Example of FAQ rich snippet on Google\" class=\"wp-image-159662\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs-300x144.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs-600x288.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs-125x60.png 125w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/search-statistics-faqs-187x90.png 187w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The FAQ rich snippets are useful for people searching for information and need quick answers to their questions. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google rich snippets are created by adding schema markup or structured data to your web pages. You can easily add schema markup to your pages using AIOSEO. For more details, please check out our guide <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-rich-snippets-to-wordpress/\">on how to add rich snippets to WordPress</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-check-for-broken-links\">9. Check for and Fix Broken Links</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A broken link is a link on your site to another webpage on your site (or other websites) that is no longer accessible. Broken links result from many issues, including typos in the URL, deleted pages, a page being moved but no redirect implemented, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Broken links negatively impact your SEO because they cause crawl errors and poor rankings. This also leads to a loss in traffic as users can&#8217;t access the URL.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that&#8217;s why you need to scan your site for broken links regularly. If you&#8217;re a WordPress user, this is easy with AIOSEO&#8217;s <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/broken-link-checker/\" title=\"Broken Link Checker\">Broken Link Checker</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This powerful plugin scans&nbsp;all the links on your site and&nbsp;lists&nbsp;all broken links. It also provides an&nbsp;easy way to fix&nbsp;all the broken links it finds.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"358\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/fix-broken-link.jpg\" alt=\"AIOSEO\'s Broken Link Checker helps you find and fix broken links on your site.\" class=\"wp-image-185998\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/fix-broken-link.jpg 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/fix-broken-link-300x153.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/fix-broken-link-600x307.jpg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/fix-broken-link-117x60.jpg 117w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/fix-broken-link-176x90.jpg 176w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You dont even need to open any web pages!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just click&nbsp;<strong>Edit URL</strong>&nbsp;to replace a broken link  right inside the plugin. You can also edit the anchor text at the same time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part is that the Broken Link Checker plugin automatically scans your site&nbsp;<strong>every 3 days</strong>. This ensures that you don&#8217;t miss any broken links.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/announcing-broken-link-checker-plugin/\" title=\"Announcing Broken Link Checker: Find and Fix Broken Links to Boost Your SEO\">Check out this article</a> for detailed instructions on using this game-changing tool.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-8-use-an-seo-checklist-to-optimize-your-website\">10. Use an SEO Checklist to Optimize Your Website</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You wont know how your SEO is doing and what to improve without analyzing your site. You can target critical issues and warnings before they hurt your rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEOs <strong>SEO Audit Checklist </strong>is a fantastic tool to take your SEO efforts to the next level. Best of all, its a great tool for beginners who dont know much about SEO and how to best optimize their websites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It lets you analyze your website in seconds and follow an easy-to-understand checklist to optimize your website for search engines. To start analyzing your site, navigate to the <strong>SEO Audit Checklist</strong> in the <strong>SEO Analysis</strong> settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"731\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-site-score-1-1024x731.png\" alt=\"Analyzing your overall site score in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31695\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-site-score-1-1024x731.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-site-score-1-300x214.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-site-score-1-768x548.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-site-score-1-600x429.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-site-score-1.png 1277w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>From here, you can check your SEO site score. The general rule of thumb is to aim for a score of 60 and above. If you end up with a low score, you can scroll down to the Complete SEO Checklist section and look for recommendations on improving your score.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"485\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-site-analysis.png\" alt=\"Analysis of basic SEO in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31696\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-site-analysis.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-site-analysis-300x208.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-site-analysis-600x416.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, from the above screenshot, this website is missing some critical areas of basic SEO. Now that you know these problems, you can use this checklist to fix them and raise your SEO score to get higher rankings.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/seo-audit-checklist/\">SEO Audit Checklist feature page</a> to learn more about this fantastic SEO tool.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-9-spy-on-your-competitors-and-steal-their-keyword-ideas\">11. Spy on Your Competitors and Steal Their Keyword Ideas</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A great way to get ahead of your competition is to do an SEO competitor analysis and steal your competitor&#8217;s keyword ideas.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When analyzing whats working for your competitors, you&#8217;ll get insight into the successful strategies others use in your market. And by finding the keywords that give your competitors the highest ROI (Return on Investment), you can use this information to improve your own SEO efforts and gain an edge.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEOs <strong>Analyze Competitor Site</strong> tool lets you spy on your competitors with a single click. Enter your competitors website URL in the <strong>Enter Competitor URL</strong> field, and press the <strong>Analyze</strong> button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"542\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-competitor-analysis-analyze-competitor-site.png\" alt=\"Analyzing your competitor\'s SEO in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31697\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-competitor-analysis-analyze-competitor-site.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-competitor-analysis-analyze-competitor-site-300x223.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-competitor-analysis-analyze-competitor-site-600x445.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Your competitors SEO analysis will show up in the same window, and you can see what keywords theyre using and get valuable WordPress SEO tips. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also compare other important SEO metrics, like page title, description, and page load speed.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is valuable if you want to improve your SEO efforts and gain an edge over your competitors. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more details, you can check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/\">how to do an SEO competitor analysis.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"3 Things You Can Do RIGHT NOW to Improve Your Search Rankings\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/33PxDasx5cU?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"site-speed-seo-hacks\">Site Speed SEO Hacks: Optimize for Speed and User Experience (UX)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Google has confirmed that site speed is a ranking factor on both desktop and mobile, so your website must be fast enough to provide a good user experience. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s look at a few things you can do to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/10-quick-easy-ways-to-speed-up-your-site/\" title=\"10 Ways to Speed up Your WordPress Site\">increase your site speed</a> without being a web developer next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-10-install-a-cache-plugin-to-increase-page-loading\">12. Install a Cache Plugin to Increase Page Loading</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To optimize your site for speed, you can use a cache plugin. Browser caching can help speed up your website by storing some of the larger files locally in the users web browser.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/wp-rocket/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">WP Rocket</a> offers comprehensive tools to help speed up your website, such as page caching and preloading.&nbsp;You can also use other cache plugins, such as <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-optimize/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">WP Optimize</a> or <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-fastest-cache/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">WP Fastest Cache</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more tools we recommend for improving page load speed, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-wordpress-cache-plugin/\" title=\"Best WordPress Cache Plugin: 7 Powerful Tools to Speed Up Your Site\">check out this article</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-11-compress-your-images-to-reduce-file-size\">13. Compress Your Images to Reduce File Size</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Compressing your images to reduce your sites overall file size is crucial for SEO since it affects your page loading. A website thats large in file size gets heavy and will take longer to load.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fortunately, you can speed up your page loading by compressing your images. Youll also decrease your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-reduce-bounce-rate/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">bounce rate</a> from users who dont have the patience to wait for your site to finish loading.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To compress your images, you can use free services, such as:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://tinypng.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">TinyPNG</a> for PNG &amp; JPG files</li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://compressjpeg.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">CompressJPEG</a> for JPG files</li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://imagecompressor.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Optimizilla</a> for PNG &amp; JPG files</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This can reduce your image file size by 70% and more, which will significantly impact your site speed.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-12-use-a-cdn-to-improve-site-speed-even-more\">14. Use a CDN to Improve Site Speed Even More</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you want to take your site speed efforts to the next level, you can use a CDN (Content Delivery Network) to serve a cached version of your site from the server closest to your geographical location.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This will help speed up your website because it limits the number of internet hops it takes to display your content from your original server (your web hosting provider).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To learn more about CDN and how to connect your site, you can check out WPBeginners guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-install-wordpress-cdn-solution-maxcdn/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">installing and setting up WordPress CDN</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-13-make-your-site-mobile-friendly-using-a-responsive-theme\">15. Make Your Site Mobile-Friendly Using a Responsive Theme</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/studiopress-authority-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"379\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/authoritypro-responsive-wordpress-theme.jpg\" alt=\"Authority Pro responsive WordPress theme\" class=\"wp-image-31698\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/authoritypro-responsive-wordpress-theme.jpg 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/authoritypro-responsive-wordpress-theme-300x156.jpg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/authoritypro-responsive-wordpress-theme-600x312.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The rise of mobile devices has made failure to look after mobile SEO a death sentence. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don&#8217;t stop breathing now&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;it&#8217;s not as bad as it seems. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If your site isnt optimized for mobile, Google will still show it. But it&#8217;ll rank mobile-friendly sites higher because of its mobile-first index. With mobile-first-index means that Google mainly uses the mobile version of your content to index and rank your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That being the case, the easiest way to make your site mobile-friendly is to use a responsive WordPress theme that adapts to different screen sizes and devices. To find a responsive theme, please visit WPForms post on the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-responsive-wordpress-themes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">60+ best responsive WordPress themes</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"content-seo-hacks\">Content SEO Hacks: Get Traffic From Existing Content</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that you can increase your organic traffic just by updating your existing or old content?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the right content SEO strategy, you can rank higher in search results for your existing content, increase CTR, and drive more organic traffic to your website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few easy content SEO tips that can have major effects on your rankings!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-14-use-long-tail-keywords-to-get-more-organic-traffic\">16. Use Long-Tail Keywords to Get More Organic Traffic</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"320\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/search-deman-curve-long-tail-keywords-768x320-1.png\" alt=\"Search demand curve infographic\" class=\"wp-image-31700\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/search-deman-curve-long-tail-keywords-768x320-1.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/search-deman-curve-long-tail-keywords-768x320-1-300x125.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/search-deman-curve-long-tail-keywords-768x320-1-600x250.png 600w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that long-tail keywords make up for 70% of search traffic? So if you want to get more organic traffic, you should definitely use long-tail keywords in your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But what are long-tail keywords really?<br><br>Long-tail keywords are phrases people enter into search engines when theyre looking for something specific. Often, they&#8217;re 3 or more words. And they can help increase your organic traffic, dominate search rankings, and boost your conversions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lets say a user wants to purchase running shoes. An example of a long-tail keyword would be: <strong>buy running shoes for flat feet</strong>. On the other hand, a short-tail keyword would be: <strong>buy shoes</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-optimizing-your-content-for-long-tail-keywords\">Optimizing Your Content for Long-Tail Keywords</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, you can add long-tail keywords and even get an SEO analysis of how well youve optimized them in your content. All you need to do is enter your long-tail keyword in the <strong>Focus Keyphrase</strong> field and press <strong>Enter</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"419\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/keyword-analysis-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Focus keyphrase analysis in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31703\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/keyword-analysis-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/keyword-analysis-in-all-in-one-seo-300x172.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/keyword-analysis-in-all-in-one-seo-600x344.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO then checks how well youve used it in your content and gives recommendations on improvements. This is so that you can maximize your rankings in search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-15-improve-readability-and-keep-visitors-on-your-site\">17. Improve Readability and Keep Visitors on Your Site</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that users spend less than a second deciding whether they want to stay on a page or not? Thats why your content has to be interesting, engaging, and easy to read so that the readers want to stay glued to your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Readability is also an important factor for search engines. As mentioned earlier, content thats easier to read often ranks higher than content thats difficult to read. It also lowers your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-bounce-rate-in-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">bounce rate</a>, and Google sees your site as more relevant.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thats why you should always break up your content with shorter sentences, subheadings, images, quotes, and bullet listsanything that will keep the reader glued to your content and stay on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-improve-readability-using-aioseo\">Improve Readability Using AIOSEO</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO automatically analyzes readability issues and makes suggestions on how you can improve your content in the <strong>Page Analysis</strong> section. Simply click on the <strong>Readability</strong> tab and it will show a list of what you&#8217;ve done well and what needs to be improved.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"551\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-page-analysis-readability.png\" alt=\"Readability analysis in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31704\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-page-analysis-readability.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-page-analysis-readability-300x226.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/aioseo-page-analysis-readability-600x453.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here you can see that this blog post has 4 readability errors that need to be fixed and recommendations on how to improve your content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Use AIOSEO&#8217;s <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/blog-post-seo-checklist/#focus-on-readability\">readability analysis tool</a> to improve your content, and youll keep visitors glued to your site in no time.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-16-help-google-discover-your-new-content-with-internal-linking\">18. Help Google Discover Your New Content With Internal Linking</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"591\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Internal-linking-strategy-infographic-by-mpdigitalmarketing.png\" alt=\"Internal linking strategy infographic by MP Digital Marketing\" class=\"wp-image-31912\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Internal-linking-strategy-infographic-by-mpdigitalmarketing.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Internal-linking-strategy-infographic-by-mpdigitalmarketing-300x243.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Internal-linking-strategy-infographic-by-mpdigitalmarketing-600x486.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Its important to have a good internal link structure for SEO. This helps visitors navigate your site, and it also helps Google to discover your new content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are two main methods for building a good internal link profile:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>Always include relevant internal links to your own content whenever publishing a new piece of content. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>And on a regular basis (weekly or monthly), update your older content to add links to newer content.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>This will help your readers and Google discover how all your content is related. And to make sure Google knows about all your links and ranks your content, you need to write descriptive anchor texts. &nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 id=\"aioseo-internal-linking-made-easy-with-aioseo\">Internal Linking Made Easy with AIOSEO</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO&#8217;s awesome <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/internal-link-assistant/\" title=\"Link Assistant\">Link Assistant</a> feature will help you automatically find new internal linking opportunities. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It will crawl all of the pages on your site and generate a <strong>Links Report</strong> with insights like:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Linking Opportunities</strong>  Recommendations of relevant posts and pages you can link to internally, as well as anchor text you can use.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Orphan Pages</strong>  Discover all of your orphan pages (pages that have no internal links) and suggestions of articles you can link to. </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"293\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/rsz_links-report.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-78679\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/rsz_links-report.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/rsz_links-report-300x126.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/rsz_links-report-600x251.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/rsz_links-report-143x60.png 143w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/rsz_links-report-215x90.png 215w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You don&#8217;t even need to edit individual posts and manually add the links yourself. Simply select the link suggestions you want to apply to your content and click the <strong>Add Link</strong> button. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"700\" height=\"307\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/link-assistant-inbound-internal-links-1.png\" alt=\"The tool gives you link suggestions and enables you to add internal links automatically.\" class=\"wp-image-77646\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/link-assistant-inbound-internal-links-1.png 700w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/link-assistant-inbound-internal-links-1-300x132.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/link-assistant-inbound-internal-links-1-600x263.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s that easy! The Link Assistant will <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ways-link-assistant-can-save-you-time-on-internal-and-external-link-building/\" title=\"save a ton of time on internal link building\">save a ton of time on internal link building</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-17-repurpose-your-existing-content-into-a-podcast\">19. Repurpose Your Existing Content Into a Podcast</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another simple way of repurposing your content is to turn it into podcasts. Through podcasts, you can use your content to build a community and then direct them to your website for more information. This will help boost your rankings and drive more traffic to your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To create a podcast, you dont have to do anything fancy. In fact, you can simply read out your blog posts, record the audio, and then upload it to your website using a <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-podcasting-plugins/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">WordPress podcast plugin</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then you can submit your podcast to platforms like iTunes and Google Play to attract an audience and ask them to visit your website. For more details, you can check out WPBeginners step-by-step guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/step-by-step-guide-how-to-start-a-podcast-with-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to start a podcast</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-18-get-conversational-and-optimize-for-voice-search\">20. Get Conversational and Optimize for Voice Search</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"706\" height=\"384\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-voice-search.png\" alt=\"Google voice search\" class=\"wp-image-31705\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-voice-search.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-voice-search-300x163.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-voice-search-704x384.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-voice-search-600x326.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Voice search is quickly becoming one of the most popular ways consumers search for products and services online. Its now more convenient for people to talk on their phones or smart speakers instead of opening Google whenever they have questions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, did you know that 45 million people use voice assistants daily, and Google Assistant usage has increased by <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/100-seo-statistics/#voice-search-seo-statistics\">400%</a> in the last year?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With this in mind, we bet you&#8217;re now wondering how to optimize your site for voice search.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To optimize your site for voice search, you need to start with the following two steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>Try and figure out what a consumer will likely say instead of type. Strangely enough, these two things are often different, so choosing the right keywords for voice optimization is important. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Focus on publishing conversational content on your site and write as you believe users will speak. </li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>These tips will help boost your rankings, increase traffic, and encourage more engagement with your content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-19-increase-conversions-by-linking-your-rss-feed\">21. Increase Conversions by Linking Your RSS Feed</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know you can increase conversions by linking to the highest-converting pages in your RSS feed?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>RSS (Really Simple Syndication or Rich Site Summary) is a web feed that allows users and applications to receive regular updates from a website or blog they&#8217;ve subscribed to.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Its a simple XML text file that includes a sites updated information, which gets plugged into a feed reader that users can subscribe to.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress comes with built-in default RSS feeds. But you can tweak and control the default feeds to increase conversions using AIOSEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the <strong>RSS Content Settings</strong>, you can add text and links before or after your content.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"363\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/rss-content-tags-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Editing the RSS feed in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-31706\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/rss-content-tags-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/rss-content-tags-in-all-in-one-seo-300x149.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/rss-content-tags-in-all-in-one-seo-600x298.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can click on the tag you want to add, and the link will be included in your feed. Or you can type in text straight into the field.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a great way to direct your readers to your most converting pages and grow your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-20-optimize-your-video-content-and-rank-in-video-search\">22. Optimize Your Video Content and Rank in Video Search</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"308\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-video-search.png\" alt=\"Google video search\" class=\"wp-image-31707\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-video-search.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-video-search-300x127.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/google-video-search-600x253.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/video-marketing-statistics-what-you-must-know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">87%</a> of video marketers say video has increased traffic to their website, and 80% say it directly helped to increase sales. Like you probably understand, videos are a great way to grow your website traffic and business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding videos to your website can also help with:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Increasing Your CTR (Click-Through-Rate) </strong> including video on your site drives a <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">157%</a> increase in organic traffic.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Lowering Your Bounce Rate</strong>  people spend over twice as long on a page with video than without.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Help You Get More Quality Backlinks </strong> the higher the quality of your content, the more likely you are to get quality backlinks.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>That being the case, you must optimize your video content to help Google find your videos and rank them in video searches. And a first step is to create a video sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is super easy with the help of AIOSEO!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have AIOSEOs <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Pro</a> version, the video sitemap is enabled by default. To learn how to configure your video sitemap, please visit our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-video-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/\">how to create a video sitemap in WordPress the easy way</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-monitor-content-performance\">23. Monitor Content and Keyword Performance</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once your content is live, you should track its performance on SERPs. This is important as it:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Helps you see if your SEO strategy is working</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Spot and combat content decay</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gives you insight into content that needs better optimization</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>All this can be done right from your WordPress dashboard using AIOSEO&#8217;s Search Statistics module. This is AIOSEO&#8217;s Google Search Console (GSC) integration and gives users <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-seo-data-to-boost-search-rankings/\">valuable SEO data</a> to help monitor campaign performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"373\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-search-statistics.png\" alt=\"Search Statistics dashboard.\" class=\"wp-image-186014\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-search-statistics.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-search-statistics-300x159.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-search-statistics-600x319.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-search-statistics-113x60.png 113w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-search-statistics-169x90.png 169w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Some reports you get from this powerful module include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>SEO Statistics</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Keyword Rankings</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Content Rankings</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>These give you a lot of metrics you can use to gauge your performance, identify issues like content decay, and give you insights into how to improve your campaigns. All these will help you boost your SEO, traffic, and engagement.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information on how to use Search Statistics to boost your SEO, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/search-statistics-power-hacks-to-help-boost-your-rankings/\" title=\"6 Search Statistics Power Hacks to Help Boost Your Rankings\">check out this guide</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"social-networks-seo-hacks\">Social Networks SEO Hacks: Get More Referral Traffic</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Social networks SEO includes the things you&#8217;re doing to optimize your social media networks to get more referral traffic to your website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It also helps you get more visibility online and can strengthen your brand. Let&#8217;s look at some quick and easy hacks to boost your social media SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-21-let-google-know-about-your-social-media-profiles\">24. Let Google Know About Your Social Media Profiles</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing your social media is important because it can strengthen your brand. Youll gain more visibility and can generate more leads for your business. Also, the more your content is shared on social media, the more people will see and link to it.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>More importantly, itll also help you get more visibility in search. After all, your social media profiles are often ranked on the first page of the search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO lets you connect up to 11 <strong>Social Profiles</strong> to let Google know which social media profiles are associated with your website:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"587\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-social-networks-social-profiles.png\" alt=\"Social networks settings in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-24649\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-social-networks-social-profiles.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-social-networks-social-profiles-300x241.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/aioseo-social-networks-social-profiles-600x482.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply paste the URLs to your social media profiles, and AIOSEO will let search engines know about them.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-22-add-twitter-cards-and-facebook-thumbnails\">25. Add Twitter Cards and Facebook Thumbnails </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding Twitter Cards and Facebook thumbnails on your website lets you control how your content looks when shared on social media.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It lets you choose the image and text displayed, which means that more people will likely notice your content and click on it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, this is a Twitter Card when sharing WPBeginners post on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/step-by-step-guide-how-to-start-a-podcast-with-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">how to start your own podcast</a> on Twitter:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"435\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wpbeginner-twitter-card-example-1.png\" alt=\"Example of summary with large image twitter card in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-23817\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wpbeginner-twitter-card-example-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wpbeginner-twitter-card-example-1-300x179.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wpbeginner-twitter-card-example-1-600x358.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, it looks appealing, and you can include more information about your content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Heres another example of what <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-twitter-cards-in-wordpress/\">one of our posts</a> looks like after choosing which thumbnail thats used when its shared on Facebook:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"449\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-facebook-thumbnail.png\" alt=\"Example of facebook thumbnail in All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-186670\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-facebook-thumbnail.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-facebook-thumbnail-300x192.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-facebook-thumbnail-600x384.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-facebook-thumbnail-94x60.png 94w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/seo-hacks-facebook-thumbnail-141x90.png 141w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These nice-looking thumbnails capture peoples interest, which makes them more likely to click on and share your content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Twitter Cards and Facebook thumbnails, youll also ensure that the right featured image is shown when your content is shared on social media. Best of all, it&#8217;ll increase referral traffic to your site.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO makes this super easy and enables Twitter Cards and Facebook thumbnails by default upon activation. But if you want to customize them and add extra information, you can check out our guides on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/add-twitter-cards-in-wordpress/\">how to add Twitter Cards in WordPress</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-fix-wrong-facebook-thumbnail-in-wordpress/\">how to fix the wrong Facebook thumbnail</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-23-add-social-feeds-to-your-site-and-improve-organic-reach\">26. Add Social Feeds to Your Site and Improve Organic Reach&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As mentioned, you can use the power of social media to boost your websites search engine rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With over half of the worlds population using social media, it makes sense to optimize your social media marketing to improve your websites organic reach on Google.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And since social media profiles rank high in the search results, they can help your site rank higher when you add social media feeds to your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, instead of adding a plain social media button, you can embed your social media feed on your WordPress site using a social media feed plugin like <a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Smash Balloon</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"706\" height=\"388\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/smashballoon-facebook-feed-slider-wordpress-example.png\" alt=\"Example of facebook feed in Smash Balloon\" class=\"wp-image-31708\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/smashballoon-facebook-feed-slider-wordpress-example.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/smashballoon-facebook-feed-slider-wordpress-example-300x165.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/smashballoon-facebook-feed-slider-wordpress-example-704x388.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/smashballoon-facebook-feed-slider-wordpress-example-600x330.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It lets you create completely customizable social media feeds tailored to your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, unlike regular social media plugins, Smash Balloon adds dynamic, indexed, and search engine crawlable content to your site. This will help boost your SEO even further.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Smash Balloon also lets you showcase your user-generated content, which we&#8217;ll look at next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-24-encourage-user-generated-content-and-get-free-marketing\">27. Encourage User-Generated Content and Get Free Marketing</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"586\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/ugc-example-monsterinsights-review.png\" alt=\"Example of user generated content in form of product reviews\" class=\"wp-image-31924\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/ugc-example-monsterinsights-review.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/ugc-example-monsterinsights-review-300x241.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/ugc-example-monsterinsights-review-600x482.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>UGC or user-generated content is any content thats been created by users, contributors, or your raving fans. If used correctly, its free marketing for your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, people tend to trust user-generated content more since its coming directly from users and not the brand itself. That said, you should take advantage of the power of user-generated content to get free marketing and increase profits for your business.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>How to do this, you may ask?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, you can encourage users to engage and post about your brand by creating a contest that encourages them to post pictures about your products and share their thoughts. And then you re-publish it on your website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>More importantly, reviews or testimonials are one of the best forms of user-generated content to help grow your business. This is evident because <a href=\"https://trustpulse.com/social-proof-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">91%</a> of millennials trust reviews as much as recommendations from friends and family.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So a good way of showcasing your Facebook reviews is by using a <a href=\"https://smashballoon.com/how-to-add-a-social-media-review-widget-to-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">social media review widget</a> in your sidebar on your website:</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"620\" height=\"399\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sidebar-testimonials.png\" alt=\"Example of Smash Balloon\'s facebook reviews sidebar widget\" class=\"wp-image-31709\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sidebar-testimonials.png 620w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sidebar-testimonials-300x193.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/sidebar-testimonials-600x386.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>This will help you build credibility and boost conversions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also encourage people to comment on your blog posts to boost your SEO. Google will see your site as relevant and bump it in the search results, which we&#8217;ll look at next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-25-reply-to-comments-and-get-more-returning-visitors\">28. Reply to Comments and Get More Returning Visitors&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that 77 million new <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/to-allow-blog-comments-or-not-heres-what-the-data-shows/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">blog comments</a> are generated by readers each month?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Comments left by users show their interest in your content, whether positive or negative. That being the case, your blog should be a two-way communication, and encouraging readers to engage can benefit your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not only does responding to comments deepen your relationship with your users, but its also a form of social proof.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Better yet, comments are user-generated content filled with long-tail keywords, which are more specific and easier to rank for. As you already know, long-tail keywords make up 70% of all search traffic.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, if you provide helpful answers to comments, its a great way of getting returning visitors to your site since users often want to come back and look for your answer:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"706\" height=\"508\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-comment-for-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"30 SEO hacks guaranteed to grow your traffic - respond to comments\" class=\"wp-image-31710\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-comment-for-all-in-one-seo.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-comment-for-all-in-one-seo-300x216.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-comment-for-all-in-one-seo-600x432.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you include links to your content when you reply, youll also boost your internal linking.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Best of all, studies have shown that users leaving comments are more likely to share your content on social media, subscribe to your channels, and buy from you.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In other words, allowing comments on your website and carefully responding to them can help increase your organic traffic and improve rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"local-seo-hacks\">Local SEO Hacks: Boost Rankings on Google Maps</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Local SEO is what you do to improve your rankings on Google Maps and get featured in Google&#8217;s Knowledge Panel. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s a must for businesses that serve customers in a specific location or have several locations and want to improve rankings in local search. This will help local customers find your brick-and-mortar stores or local services.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few powerful hacks that will boost your local SEO and rankings in local search!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-26-get-featured-on-googles-knowledge-panel-and-google-maps\">29. Get Featured on Googles Knowledge Panel and Google Maps</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If youre running a brick-and-mortar store or offering your services in a specific location, you should create a Business Profile in <a href=\"https://www.google.com/business/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Google My Business</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business Profiles are specific to businesses that serve customers at a particular location or within a designated service area.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Why is this important for SEO, you may ask?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A Google My Business profile is important for SEO because it lets you be more visible in local search and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-embed-google-maps-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Easily Embed Google Maps in WordPress\">Google Maps</a>, where potential customers can easily find your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Youll have your own profile, where you can add your businesss information, photos, and showcase reviews straight from the search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, when people search for a business (for example, Walmart Pharmacy), Google may show a Knowledge Graph card with the nearby locations for Walmarts Pharmacy:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"592\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/example-of-google-knowledge-graph-card.png\" alt=\"Example of Google Knowledge Graph card \" class=\"wp-image-30099\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/example-of-google-knowledge-graph-card.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/example-of-google-knowledge-graph-card-300x243.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/example-of-google-knowledge-graph-card-600x487.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This makes it easy for people to find your brick-and-mortar locations and puts your company at the top of the results. Best of all, this will increase the clickthrough rate of your site and likely lead to more sales for your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To increase your chances of getting featured in Googles Knowledge Panel, add Googles <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-add-local-business-schema-in-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Add Local Business Schema in WordPress\">local business structured data</a> or schema markup to your website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEOs Local Business Schema addon, you can easily set this up and increase your rankings in the local search results, Google Maps, and the Knowledge panel in no time. For more details, please visit our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/local-business-seo/\">local business SEO documentation</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-27-build-and-optimize-your-citations\">30. Build and Optimize Your Citations</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Citations are important because they help Google to trust your business and show it in search results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If Google sees consistent citations of your business name, address, and phone number, it counts this as trustworthy information. Conflicting info about your business can negatively impact your rankings.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing you need to do is make sure your business information is displayed on your website where its easy to find. For instance, it can be on your homepage, footer, or contact us page.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To avoid inconsistency when adding citations to other sites, it can be good to use a Listing Management solution like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Semrush</a> offers:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"361\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/semrush-listing-management-solution.png\" alt=\"Semrush\'s listing management tool\" class=\"wp-image-27772\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/semrush-listing-management-solution.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/semrush-listing-management-solution-300x148.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/semrush-listing-management-solution-600x297.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All you need to do is enter your business information, and Semrush will make sure your business info appears consistently on every major citation site on the internet (including Facebook, Google My Business, Yellow Pages, and more).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But dont forget to remove duplicate citations since they can push your rankings down due to inconsistencies in data.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-get-local-seo-citations/\" title=\"How to Get Local SEO Citations and Business Directory Listings (Beginners Guide)\">Check out this detailed guide</a> for more information on building local SEO citations.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-28-submit-your-site-to-high-quality-local-directories\">31. Submit Your Site to High-Quality Local Directories</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To increase visibility online and boost your rankings, you should also submit your site to local directories, such as Yelp and Bing.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, you should ensure theyre quality directories, or it can hurt your rankings.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/yelp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Yelp</a> is one of the most popular sites for business discovery and reviews. And getting listed on Bing can help you earn more leads for your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/yelp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"353\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/yelp-hompage.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-36576\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/yelp-hompage.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/yelp-hompage-300x145.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/yelp-hompage-600x290.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/yelp-hompage-124x60.png 124w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/yelp-hompage-186x90.png 186w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, checking <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/10322/the-ultimate-list-50-local-business-directories.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">HubSpots local business directory</a> list will help you find quality directories.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Overall, the best thing is to try and identify the local directories where your customers are and add your business to them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Dont forget to keep your business information consistent on all directories to be trusted and favored by Google. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Learn more local SEO hacks in our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/a-complete-local-seo-checklist/\" title=\"A Complete Local SEO Checklist: 10 Tips to Improve Rankings\">ultimate local SEO checklist</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"off-page-seo-hacks\">Off-Page SEO Hacks: Winning Backlink Strategies&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Off-page SEO includes what you&#8217;re doing outside of your own website to impact your rankings in search results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using the right off-page SEO hacks, you can get more referral traffic to your website, strengthen your authority online, and improve your search rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at two winning off-page SEO strategies next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-29-look-for-guest-blogging-opportunities-to-get-backlinks\">32. Look for Guest Blogging Opportunities to Get Backlinks</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Guest blogging is one of the most effective types of link building and getting more quality backlinks. Guest blogging works because you offer value to site owners in exchange for a link to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you choose your guest blogging targets carefully, you can soon build up a diverse and authoritative inbound link profile.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To guest blog effectively, you need to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Identify sites that accept guest posts</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pitch and create stellar content</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Create a bio that helps both with link building and lead generation</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Learn more in OptinMonsters <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ultimate-guide-to-guest-blogging-strategy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ultimate guide to guest blogging</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-30-create-and-add-infographics-to-your-site\">33. Create and Add Infographics to Your Site&nbsp;</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating and promoting infographics is another powerful strategy to increase website traffic, improve your domain authority, and boost your SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, creating an infographic that focuses on a trending topic and includes helpful stats and data visualizations can get people interested in sharing your infographic with others.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Heres an example of WPBeginners infographic of <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/facts-about-wordpress/?display=wide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">25 things you dont know about WordPress</a>:</p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/facts-about-wordpress/?display=wide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"596\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wpbeginner-wordpress-infographic.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-31711\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wpbeginner-wordpress-infographic.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wpbeginner-wordpress-infographic-300x245.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/wpbeginner-wordpress-infographic-600x490.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>You should create your infographic and publish it on your website so that users can link back to it. You can find tools to help you create infographics in OptinMonsters post on <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/best-visual-content-creation-tools/#info\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">51 visual content creation tools to make marketing easy</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, you shouldnt share the infographic by itself. As mentioned earlier, Google can see it as thin content if it doesnt include text as well.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So a good strategy is to publish a new post with your infographic and add some text explaining your process and your findings within the infographic. Dont forget to add an embed code to make it easy for others to share your infographic.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-use-these-30-seo-hacks-and-tips-to-boost-your-rankings-and-revenue\">Use these 30+ SEO Hacks and Tips to Boost Your Rankings and Revenue</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this post helped you discover some SEO hacks and tips to help boost your search rankings and revenue. You may also want to check out other articles on our blog, like&nbsp;our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/diy-seo-projects-for-beginners/\" title=\"DIY SEO: 4 Easy Projects to Get Started\">DIY SEO tips</a> and our guide to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-use-ai-seo-software-to-boost-rankings/\" title=\"How to Use AI SEO Software to Boost Your Rankings\">using AI SEO software to boost your rankings</a>. <br><br>If you found this article helpful, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/c/AIOSEO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">YouTube Channel</a>. Youll find many more helpful tutorials there. You can also follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/aioseopack\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/aioseo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">LinkedIn</a>, or <a href=\"https://facebook.com/aioseopack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">Facebook</a> to stay in the loop.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-content-justification-center is-layout-flex wp-container-4 wp-block-buttons\"></div>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/seo-hacks-to-grow-your-traffic/\">30+ SEO Hacks Guaranteed to Grow Your Traffic</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"https://aioseo.com/seo-hacks-to-grow-your-traffic/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"DIY SEO: 4 Easy Projects to Get Started\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base